          "content": "What is ihip",
          "created_at": 1774358339.7155426
        },
        {
          "id": "b5e8d41c-73f8-4d44-9b3b-0932d1a73ac3",
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "â€œIHIPâ€ can mean a few different things depending on context. Most commonly:\n\n- **Individualized Home Instruction Plan** â€” in education, especially for homeschooling in some U.S. states like New York.\n- **Indian Health Improvement Program** â€” a healthcare-related term.\n- **Integrated Health Information Platform** â€” used in public health/data systems.\n\nIf you mean the homeschooling one, an **IHIP** is a document parents submit that outlines:\n\n- the studentâ€™s name and grade\n- the subjects to be taught\n- the instructional plan for the year\n\nItâ€™s basically a yearly homeschool plan.\n\nIf you want, I can explain the **homeschool IHIP** in simple terms or show you a sample.",
          "created_at": 1774358343.4645085,
          "router_meta": {
            "mode": "general",
            "intent": "conversation",
            "confidence": null,
            "reason": "Defaulted to general conversation.",
